section.section:
In this subsection, "housing for older persons" means housing:
provided under any State or federal program that is specifically designed and operated to assist elderly persons, as defined in the State or federal program;
intended for, and solely occupied by, persons who are at least 62 years old;
intended and operated for occupancy by at least one person who is at least 55 years old in each unit; or
that meets the requirements set forth in regulations adopted by the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development under 42 U.S.C. § 3607(b)(2)(C).
